TITLE: Updating Connection Targets with Header Mapping - JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet demonstrates how to update connection targets with explicit header mapping to maintain specific content types after the default content-type header mapping was removed. It showcases the structure for defining targetActorSelection, headers, and piggybackCommand with a createConnection type, including detailed header mappings for content-type, correlation-id, and reply-to.
SOURCE: https://github.com/eclipse-ditto/ditto/blob/master/documentation/src/main/resources/pages/ditto/release_notes_200.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
    "targetActorSelection": "/system/sharding/connection",
    "headers": {
        "aggregate": false
    },
    "piggybackCommand": {
        "type": "connectivity.commands:createConnection",
            "connection": {
              "targets":[{
                "headerMapping": {
                  "content-type": "{%raw%}{{header:content-type}}{%endraw%}",
                  "correlation-id": "{%raw%}{{header:correlation-id}}{%endraw%}",
                  "reply-to": "{%raw%}{{header:reply-to}}{%endraw%}"
                },
                // ...
              }]
              // ...
            }
    }
}
```

