TITLE: Utilizing ByteBuffer.js for JavaScript Byte Manipulation
DESCRIPTION: This snippet showcases the use of ByteBuffer.js for buffered byte manipulations in JavaScript. It converts ArrayBuffer to base64 and back, reads integers and UTF-8 strings, and demonstrates buffer offset handling, facilitating advanced byte-manipulation tasks in JavaScript environments.
